Important commands for shell scripting 


Head -> Prints First(old) messages 
Example
cat /var/log/messages | head  (Prints first 10 lines of /var/log/messages)
head /var/log/messages        (Prints first 10 lines of /var/log/messages)
head -n 20 /var/log/messages  (Prints first 20 lines of /var/log/messages. Similarly any number of first n number of lines can be printed)

Tail -> Prints Last (latest) messages
Example 
cat /var/log/messages | tail  (Prints first 10 lines of /var/log/messages)
tail /var/log/messages        (Prints first 10 lines of /var/log/messages)
tail -n 20 /var/log/messages  (Prints first 20 lines of /var/log/messages. Similarly any number of first n number of lines can be printed)

